description: The Snake Sultan Nature Documentary hosted by Martin Hommel, published by Autentic in 2014 - English narration http://docuwiki.net/images/2/27/The-Snake-Sultan-Cover.jpg Information ------------------------------ The Snake Sultan Iranians call him "the Snake Sultan". This man from the nomadic tribe of the "Bakhtiari" catches poisonous snakes with his bare hands and delivers them to the Iranian central Serum institute for production of anti-venom. He is accompanied by his sons Ali (8 years) and Hassan (6 years). After they had reached the age of six months, he built up their resistance by injecting them tiny amounts of snake poison. They have grown up with snakes and have no fear even from the most toxic ones.
